  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. The model was revised on 2025-11-10 to update the impeller geometry parameterisation and turbulence model constants; the primary experimental hemolysis dataset retains a dataVintage of 2025-10-17, predating that revision. The assessment narrative argues the geometry change was not material to the dataset's applicability, but no formal re-validation against the updated model build was conducted. Decision: Accepted.",
  "modelRevisionDate": "2025-11-10T00:00:00Z",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-claim",
