      "type": "Dataset",
      "name": "FDA Generic Centrifugal Pump — Experimental Hemolysis Measurements (Pre-Revision Build)",
      "description": "In-vitro hemolysis index measurements collected across 5 flow-speed operating points using a porcine blood analogue in the FDA generic centrifugal pump test rig. Data were acquired and curated prior to the November 2025 model revision. The assessment narrative states the impeller geometry parameterisation change introduced in revision v2 is a minor smoothing adjustment that does not alter the bulk flow topology, and therefore the pre-revision dataset remains representative. No formal sensitivity study or re-validation run was performed against the updated model build to substantiate this claim.",
      "dataVintage": "2025-10-17T00:00:00Z",
      "source": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4058821"
    },
